                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1123 Coltman, Charles/38: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-02-13T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 13, 1923—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. Your No. 48 February 11, 8 p.m.</p>
                <p>The Department fully concurs in your opinion that the reply of the Foreign Office
                    is wholly unsatisfactory. Please give me your views on Department’s telegram No.
                    21, January 31, 6 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
